WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:04.803
Child:
COME ON, COME ON!

00:04.805 --> 00:08.407
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

00:20.520 --> 00:21.887
HERE YOU GO.

00:21.889 --> 00:24.223
THANK YOU.
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

00:24.225 --> 00:26.025
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

00:28.361 --> 00:31.030
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

00:31.032 --> 00:33.465
[ "WE NEED A LITTLE CHRISTMAS" PLAYS ]

00:34.934 --> 00:38.237
♪ <i>HAUL OUT THE HOLLY</i> ♪
[ ALL GASP ]

00:38.239 --> 00:42.541
♪ <i>PUT UP THE TREE</i>
<i>BEFORE MY SPIRIT FALLS AGAIN</i> ♪

00:42.543 --> 00:45.644
♪ <i>FILL UP THE STOCKING</i> ♪

00:45.646 --> 00:52.384
♪ <i>I MAY BE RUSHING THINGS,</i>
<i>BUT DECK THE HALLS AGAIN NOW</i> ♪

00:52.386 --> 00:55.454
♪ <i>FOR WE NEED A LITTLE CHRISTMAS</i> ♪

00:55.456 --> 00:57.189
♪ <i>RIGHT THIS VERY MINUTE</i> ♪

00:57.191 --> 01:00.726
♪ <i>CANDLES IN THE WINDOW,</i>
<i>CAROLS AT THE SPINET</i> ♪

01:00.728 --> 01:03.295
♪ <i>YES, WE NEED A LITTLE CHRISTMAS</i> ♪
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

01:03.297 --> 01:05.197
♪ <i>RIGHT THIS VERY MINUTE</i> ♪

01:05.199 --> 01:06.999
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
♪ <i>IT HASN'T SNOWED  SINGLE FLURRY</i> ♪

01:07.001 --> 01:08.934
♪ <i>BUT, SANTA DEAR, WE'RE IN A HURRY</i> ♪

01:08.936 --> 01:11.770
♪ <i>CLIMB DOWN THE CHIMNEY</i> ♪

01:11.772 --> 01:14.339
LOOKS LIKE YOU MISSED
YOUR CUE. [ CHUCKLES ]
♪ <i>TURN ON</i>
<i>THE BRIGHTEST STRING OF</i> ♪

01:14.341 --> 01:16.408
♪ <i>LIGHTS I'VE EVER SEEN</i> ♪

01:16.410 --> 01:19.078
♪ <i>SLICE UP THE FRUITCAKE</i> ♪

01:34.828 --> 01:38.630
♪ <i>GROWN A LITTLE LEANER,</i>
<i>GROWN A LITTLE COLDER</i> ♪

01:38.632 --> 01:41.667
♪ <i>GROWN A LITTLE SADDER,</i>
<i>GROWN A LITTLE OLDER</i> ♪

01:41.669 --> 01:45.704
♪ <i>AND I NEED A LITTLE ANGEL</i>
<i>SITTING ON MY SHOULDER</i> ♪

01:45.706 --> 01:48.941
♪ <i>NEED A LITTLE CHRISTMAS NOW</i> ♪

02:02.522 --> 02:04.123
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

02:06.126 --> 02:09.428
♪ <i>FOR WE NEED A LITTLE MUSIC</i> ♪
[ DOG BARKS ]

02:09.430 --> 02:11.997
LOU! LOU, THAT GUY
JUST ROBBED US!
♪ <i>NEED A LITTLE LAUGHTER</i> ♪

02:11.999 --> 02:13.665
♪ <i>NEED A LITTLE SINGING</i> ♪

02:13.667 --> 02:15.400
SANTA!
♪ <i>RINGING THROUGH THE RAFTER</i> ♪

02:15.402 --> 02:19.671
♪ <i>AND WE NEED A LITTLE SNAPPY</i>
<i>HAPPY EVER AFTER</i> ♪

02:19.673 --> 02:24.376
♪ <i>NEED A LITTLE CHRISTMAS NOW</i> ♪

02:24.378 --> 02:25.677
[ GUNSHOT ]

02:25.679 --> 02:28.580
[ PEOPLE SCREAMING ]

02:29.616 --> 02:30.782
[ GUNSHOTS ]

02:30.784 --> 02:32.017
DROP YOUR WEAPON!

02:32.019 --> 02:33.285
[ GUNSHOT ]

02:39.826 --> 02:42.027
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

02:46.633 --> 02:48.901
Lou:
MY GRANDKIDS ARE GONNA HATE ME.

02:48.903 --> 02:50.903
I KILLED SANTA CLAUS.

02:50.905 --> 02:54.273
DIDN'T YOU SAY HE WAS FIRING
AT ALL THE OTHER SANTAS?

02:54.275 --> 02:56.508
YES.
SHOOTING WILD.

02:56.510 --> 02:59.645
THEN YOU SAVED CHRISTMAS,

02:59.647 --> 03:04.283
AND THAT MAKES YOU
AN AMERICAN HERO.

03:04.285 --> 03:05.817
AND US A WHOLE LOT SAFER.

03:05.819 --> 03:08.687
NOW, THIS OFFICER IS GOING
TO ESCORT YOU DOWNTOWN

03:08.689 --> 03:10.389
AND TAKE YOUR STATEMENT.

03:10.391 --> 03:12.090
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

03:18.531 --> 03:21.066
OKAY, VICTIM'S I.D.
SAYS HIS NAME

03:21.068 --> 03:24.069
IS GEORGE O'CONNOR
FROM TIOGA, NORTH DAKOTA.

03:24.071 --> 03:27.206
BORN 1950,
WHICH MAKES HIM --
[ RINGTONE PLAYING ]

03:27.208 --> 03:29.374
TOO OLD TO BE ROBBING
OUT-OF-STATE BANKS

03:29.376 --> 03:30.742
LIKE JESSE JAMES.

03:30.744 --> 03:33.812
GOOD HEAVENS.
HOW MANY TIMES CAN SHE CALL ME?

03:33.814 --> 03:36.682
DOESN'T SHE HAVE
THE DAY OFF?

03:36.684 --> 03:38.617
SYKES.

03:38.619 --> 03:39.885
OH.

03:39.887 --> 03:42.221
ASSISTANT BANK MANAGER
SAID SHE PUT 120 GRAND

03:42.223 --> 03:44.623
AND EXPLODING DYE PACKS
INTO SANTA'S SACK,

03:44.625 --> 03:45.991
BUT IT'S EMPTY.

03:45.993 --> 03:48.360
WELL, MAYBE GEORGIE HERE
HAD A HAND-OFF SET UP

03:48.362 --> 03:49.761
WITH AN ACCOMPLICE.
YEAH.

03:49.763 --> 03:51.830
BUT IN MY
RESERVE TRAINING CLASS,

03:51.832 --> 03:53.265
THEY TELL US THAT
THE DYE PACKS SHOULD EXPLODE

03:53.267 --> 03:54.833
WHEN THEY GO THROUGH
THE BANK DOOR, RIGHT?

03:54.835 --> 03:56.468
THERE'S A FREQUENCY
TRANSMITTER --

03:56.470 --> 04:00.505
YET ANOTHER MYSTERY
THAT ROBBERY HOMICIDE WILL SOLVE

04:00.507 --> 04:02.374
ONCE WE TURN THIS CASE
OVER TO THEM.

04:02.376 --> 04:03.775
HOLD ON, SIR.

04:03.777 --> 04:06.578
YOU DON'T CONSIDER
THE MURDER OF SANTA CLAUS

04:06.580 --> 04:07.846
TO BE A MAJOR CRIME?

04:07.848 --> 04:10.048
BECAUSE IN MY
RESERVE TRAINING CLASS --

04:10.050 --> 04:11.984
BUZZ, THE FIRST THING
YOU HAVE TO LEARN

04:11.986 --> 04:13.652
AS A <i>BACKUP</i> POLICE OFFICER

04:13.654 --> 04:17.723
IS HOW NOT TO GET EMOTIONALLY
CAUGHT UP IN THE CRIME,

04:17.725 --> 04:20.425
WHICH, IN THIS CASE,  IS OVER.

04:20.427 --> 04:22.094
THE CIRCLE IS CLOSED.

04:22.096 --> 04:23.762
Sharon:
LIEUTENANT PROVENZA.

04:23.764 --> 04:25.597
THE CIRCLE RE-OPENS.

04:25.599 --> 04:26.999
CAPTAIN.

04:27.001 --> 04:30.769
OH,
AND YOUR <i>WHOLE </i> FAMILY.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.504
WHAT
A WONDERFUL SURPRISE.

04:32.506 --> 04:34.373
IS IT?
I'VE BEEN CALLING YOU.

04:34.375 --> 04:35.907
UH, MY, UH...

04:35.909 --> 04:38.777
WE WERE SHOPPING NEARBY
FOR THE CHRISTMAS PARTY,

04:38.779 --> 04:40.412
AND I HEARD
WE'D BEEN ROLLED OUT.

04:40.414 --> 04:43.615
SO, LIEUTENANT, MY UNDERSTANDING
IS THAT OUR ROBBER

04:43.617 --> 04:45.884
DRESSED UP AS SANTA,
HELD UP A BANK --

04:45.886 --> 04:48.520
AND GOT KILLED BY THE GUARD --
END OF STORY.

04:48.522 --> 04:50.188
EXCEPT WE CAN'T FIND
THE MONEY.

04:50.190 --> 04:52.291
AND WE HAVE AN ISSUE
WITH THE BODY, MA'AM.

04:52.293 --> 04:54.426
Rusty: EMILY, RICKY, AND I
CAN FINISH THE SHOPPING.

04:54.428 --> 04:56.695
THIS WON'T TAKE LONG,

04:56.697 --> 04:58.297
BUT THERE ARE SOME THINGS
NOT ON MY LIST,

04:58.299 --> 04:59.598
LIKE MY EGG-NOG RECIPE.

04:59.600 --> 05:03.669
MOM, RICKY AND I HAVE HELPED YOU
MAKE EGG NOG SINCE BIRTH.

05:03.671 --> 05:05.437
ALSO, WE NEED
TO START THE BAKING,

05:05.439 --> 05:06.872
SO IF I'M NOT THERE
BY DINNER, JUST --

05:06.874 --> 05:08.473
NOW YOU'RE NOT
MAKING DINNER TONIGHT?

05:08.475 --> 05:10.709
NO, WE CAN -- WE CAN ORDER OUT.
IT'S ALL GOOD.

05:10.711 --> 05:12.077
THANK YOU.

05:12.079 --> 05:14.079
EMILY, RICKY,
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE

05:14.081 --> 05:16.148
BEFORE WE BECOME
WITNESSES TO SOMETHING.

05:17.517 --> 05:20.085
SO, INTERESTING DETAIL --
THIS IS NOT OUR ROBBER.

05:20.087 --> 05:21.787
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT,
MIKE?

05:21.789 --> 05:23.422
UH, HERE'S
A SCREEN GRAB

05:23.424 --> 05:24.890
FROM THE BANK'S SECURITY
FOOTAGE, MA'AM.

05:24.892 --> 05:26.892
OUR ROBBER'S BEARD
WAS TOTALLY FAKE.

05:26.894 --> 05:29.461
AND OUR DEAD SANTA'S BEARD
IS THE REAL THING.

05:29.463 --> 05:31.063
Buzz: WAIT.

05:31.065 --> 05:33.999
ARE YOU SAYING THE SECURITY
GUARD SHOT THE WRONG SANTA?

05:34.001 --> 05:36.268
AND OUR ROBBER SANTA GOT AWAY,
YES.

05:36.270 --> 05:37.736
EXPLAINS WHY
WE CAN'T FIND THE CASH.

05:37.738 --> 05:39.137
WELL,
SYKES IS LOOKING FOR

05:39.139 --> 05:41.106
THE WOMAN IN CHARGE
OF OUR DANCING SANTAS --

05:41.108 --> 05:43.675
THE C-CHOREOGRAPHER,
I THINK SHE'S CALLED, MA'AM.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.410
HER NAME'S LYDIA MANNING.
[ STUTTERING ]

05:45.412 --> 05:47.212
THIS GUY HAD A GUN.

05:47.214 --> 05:50.182
NOW, WHY WOULD SOMEONE
ARM THEMSELVES FOR [STUTTERS]

05:50.184 --> 05:51.750
WHAT DO YOU CALL
THAT THING?

05:51.752 --> 05:53.685
A "FLASH MOB,"
LIEUTENANT.

05:53.687 --> 05:56.254
I'M GONNA LOOK AROUND FOR
SECURITY CAMERAS IN THE AREA --

05:56.256 --> 05:57.155
EXTRA ONES.

05:57.157 --> 05:58.824
EXCUSE ME.
THANK YOU, BUZZ.

05:58.826 --> 06:00.559
UH, LIEUTENANT,
AS YOU ALL KNOW,

06:00.561 --> 06:02.194
I'M HAVING A CHRISTMAS PARTY
TOMORROW NIGHT,

06:02.196 --> 06:04.863
AND ARE YOU --
ARE YOU COMING, BY THE WAY?

06:04.865 --> 06:06.765
N-NO, NO,
I'LL BE OUT OF TOWN.

06:06.767 --> 06:10.102
I'M GOING DOWN TO LAGUNA BEACH
WITH A, UM, UH, A-A-A FRIEND,

06:10.104 --> 06:11.970
AND -- AND IT'S
A SPUR-OF-THE-MOMENT THING.

06:11.972 --> 06:14.272
WELL, THEN, TIME IS
OF THE ESSENCE FOR ALL OF US,

06:14.274 --> 06:16.141
SO WHY DON'T WE
DIVIDE AND CONQUER?

06:16.143 --> 06:19.311
I-I'LL STAY HERE AND SEE
IF OUR MISSING-ROBBER SANTA

06:19.313 --> 06:21.713
WAS A PART OF
THIS FLASH-DANCE THING.

06:21.715 --> 06:24.249
OKAY, I'M GONNA GO DOWNTOWN
AND INTERVIEW

06:24.251 --> 06:26.651
SANTAS, WITNESSES,
BANK EMPLOYEES.

06:26.653 --> 06:28.620
YOU CAN HANDLE
THE CHOREOGRAPHER.

06:28.622 --> 06:30.956
MIKE, ANDY,
YOU COME WITH ME.

06:33.593 --> 06:36.261
UH, JUST TAKE
A QUICK LOOK, LYDIA.

06:36.263 --> 06:38.096
SEE IF YOU RECOGNIZE HIM
AT ALL.

06:38.098 --> 06:40.065
GOD. YES.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.334
YES, I-I RECOGNIZE HIM
FROM REHEARSAL.

06:42.336 --> 06:44.002
HE WAS IN THE THIRD ROW.

06:44.004 --> 06:46.872
HE CAME IN ON THE HIP THRUST
DURING THE CHORUS.

06:46.874 --> 06:48.473
I-I DON'T KNOW HIS NAME.

06:48.475 --> 06:51.443
SO, THESE DANCING SANTAS
WEREN'T FRIENDS OF YOURS, MA'AM?

06:51.445 --> 06:54.279
NO, I-I-I --
I PUT THIS FLASH MOB TOGETHER

06:54.281 --> 06:57.115
AS A WAY TO PUBLICIZE
MY NEW DANCE STUDIO.

06:57.117 --> 06:59.317
THE SANTAS WERE [SIGHS]
THEY WERE --

06:59.319 --> 07:02.554
THEY WERE MOSTLY STRANGERS
WHO RESPONDED TO AN INVITE

07:02.556 --> 07:04.156
I PUT UP ON MY WEBSITE.

07:04.158 --> 07:06.758
MAYBE I CAN ACCESS A SPREADSHEET
OF THEIR NAMES ON MY PHONE?

07:06.760 --> 07:08.126
OH, GOD.

07:09.762 --> 07:12.798
[ RINGTONE PLAYING ]

07:12.800 --> 07:15.300
YES, BUZZ, WHAT IS IT?

07:15.302 --> 07:16.301
WHAT?

07:16.303 --> 07:18.503
NO, UH, NO, NO, DON'T --
DON'T MOVE!

07:18.505 --> 07:20.172
WE'LL BE RIGHT THERE!

07:21.474 --> 07:25.977
AT FIRST I THOUGHT IT WAS OIL,
BUT THEN I SAW IT WAS RED.

07:25.979 --> 07:27.813
Provenza:
A BLOOD TRAIL.

07:27.815 --> 07:30.315
A BLOOD TRAIL.

07:30.317 --> 07:33.018
A BLOOD TRA--

07:34.287 --> 07:35.454
DAMN IT!

07:35.456 --> 07:37.289
LOOKS LIKE OUR PILE OF MONEY
HIT THE ROAD, SIR.

07:37.291 --> 07:40.659
YEAH,
WITH A BLEEDING ST. NICK.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.227
SYKES?

07:42.229 --> 07:44.329
UM, I'LL PUT OUT A MEDICAL ALERT
TO COUNTY HOSPITALS

07:44.331 --> 07:47.866
FOR ALL...
BLEEDING SANTAS.

07:47.868 --> 07:49.201
COME ON, BUZZ.

07:49.203 --> 07:52.103
I'LL HELP YOU GRAB THE CAMERAS
FROM IN HERE.

07:54.774 --> 07:58.310
Faith: AND THEN HE STEPPED UP TO
THE COUNTER AND GAVE ME A NOTE.

08:01.414 --> 08:02.514
WHAT'D THE NOTE SAY?

08:02.516 --> 08:05.650
IT SAID, "GIVE ME MONEY,
OR I'LL SHOOT."

08:05.652 --> 08:08.420
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.
I TURNED TO MEL FOR HELP.

08:08.422 --> 08:09.988
WHICH IS PROCEDURE,

08:09.990 --> 08:11.690
AS IS GIVING HIM EVERYTHING
IN THE DRAWER.

08:11.692 --> 08:12.858
HOW MUCH WAS IT?

08:12.860 --> 08:14.893
ALMOST $120,000.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.428
AROUND CHRISTMAS,

08:16.430 --> 08:18.797
THERE'S TONS OF CASH DEPOSITS
IN THE BUSINESS LINE,

08:18.799 --> 08:21.733
BUT WE'RE TRAINED
TO AVOID VIOLENCE AT ALL COSTS.

08:21.735 --> 08:24.803
OUR PRIORITY
IS CUSTOMER SAFETY.

08:24.805 --> 08:29.341
IF I HADN'T YELLED AT THE GUARD,
MAYBE NOBODY WOULD'VE BEEN...

08:30.576 --> 08:32.277
Tao:
BUZZ COLLECTED VIDEO

08:32.279 --> 08:35.146
FROM CHOREOGRAPHER
LYDIA MANNING'S
PERSONAL CAMCORDER,

08:35.148 --> 08:37.315
NINE CELLPHONES,
FOUR BANK SECURITY CAMS,

08:37.317 --> 08:40.151
BUT NOT ONE OF THEM HAS
AN ANGLE ON THE PERSON
WHO FIRED THE FIRST SHOT.

08:40.153 --> 08:41.520
Buzz:
AND YOU'LL NOTICE,

08:41.522 --> 08:43.855
AS SOON AS OUR ROBBER SANTA
LEAVES THE BANK,

08:43.857 --> 08:46.191
WE LOSE HIM IN THE CROWD.
SEE?
YEAH.

08:46.193 --> 08:48.527
AND THEN THERE'S OUR VICTIM,
GEORGE O'CONNOR.

08:48.529 --> 08:51.530
HE PULLS HIS WEAPON ON CAMERA,
SO THE FIRST SHOT WASN'T HIS.

08:51.532 --> 08:54.499
BUT JUDGING BY THE BLOOD TRAIL
IN THE GARAGE,

08:54.501 --> 08:56.601
HE MUST'VE WOUNDED
ROBBER SANTA.

08:56.603 --> 08:58.470
WHAT DO WE KNOW ABOUT
MR. O'CONNOR?

08:58.472 --> 09:00.171
OKAY, WELL, THERE'S NO PRINTS
IN THE SYSTEM.

09:00.173 --> 09:01.506
GUN IS UNREGISTERED.

09:01.508 --> 09:03.275
THE TOWN HE COMES FROM
DOESN'T HAVE A STOPLIGHT,

09:03.277 --> 09:04.543
MUCH LESS A POLICE FORCE.

09:04.545 --> 09:06.878
HE'S MARRIED --
TRYING TO FIND THE WIFE.

09:06.880 --> 09:09.481
GOOD NEWS --
JUST HEARD FROM PATROL.

09:09.483 --> 09:11.149
THEY WERE OUT
CHECKING HOSPITALS

09:11.151 --> 09:12.851
WHEN THEY SPOTTED
A GUY DRESSED AS SANTA

09:12.853 --> 09:15.420
SITTING IN HIS CAR
AROUND THE CORNER
FROM UNIVERSITY MEDICAL.

09:15.422 --> 09:17.756
HE HAD THE NOTE HE USED
IN THE BANK ROBBERY ON HIM.

09:17.758 --> 09:18.857
FANTASTIC!

09:18.859 --> 09:20.659
NOT QUITE.
HE'S DEAD.

09:21.394 --> 09:23.028
PERFECT!

09:23.030 --> 09:24.329
MYSTERY SOLVED!
JUSTICE SERVED!

09:24.331 --> 09:25.830
LET'S FILL OUT
THE PAPERWORK!

09:25.832 --> 09:29.534
HOLD ON THERE, RUDOLPH.
AMY, DID THEY FIND THE MONEY?

09:31.704 --> 09:32.904
NO.

09:32.906 --> 09:34.272
SON OF A NUTCRACKER.

09:34.274 --> 09:35.540
BUT WE DO HAVE AN I.D.

09:35.542 --> 09:37.208
ROBBER SANTA'S NAME
WAS DEAN COKER.

09:37.210 --> 09:39.077
HE WAS A GYM TRAINER,

09:39.079 --> 09:40.845
AND UNLESS THE MONEY DISAPPEARED
UP A CHIMNEY...

09:40.847 --> 09:43.415
ROBBER SANTA
HAD AN ACCOMPLICE.

09:43.417 --> 09:45.483
LET ME KNOW WHEN THE BODY
GETS TO THE MORGUE.

09:46.986 --> 09:48.987
SO...

09:48.989 --> 09:52.691
WHO IS THIS FRIEND YOU'RE
SPENDING, UH, CHRISTMAS WITH?

09:52.693 --> 09:53.925
AT THIS RATE...

09:53.927 --> 09:56.561
YOU.

10:01.000 --> 10:02.567
IT'S JUST FUNNY.

10:02.569 --> 10:04.569
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME I'VE
GONE INTO THE CHRISTMAS SEASON

10:04.571 --> 10:06.137
WITHOUT HAVING BEEN OFFERED
A CONTRACT.

10:06.139 --> 10:10.108
YOU COULD MAKE MORE MONEY
DANCING IN L.A.,

10:10.110 --> 10:12.677
AND IT WOULD GO
A LOT FURTHER, TOO!

10:12.679 --> 10:14.813
OR YOU COULD BE
A CHOREOGRAPHER FOR FLASH MOBS.

10:14.815 --> 10:16.081
AH!

10:16.083 --> 10:17.482
I HEAR THOSE PEOPLE
MAKE A KILLING.

10:17.484 --> 10:20.619
NO? TOO SOON?
RUSTY LIKED IT.

10:22.221 --> 10:23.521
MOM, WHERE'S
THE CHRISTMAS VILLAGE?

10:25.358 --> 10:26.491
THE WHAT?
Emily: IGNORE HIM, RUSTY.

10:26.493 --> 10:29.761
HE'S OBSESSED
WITH CHILDHOOD JUNK.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.563
WHOA! JUNK?

10:31.565 --> 10:32.697
NO, NO, FIRST OFF,

10:32.699 --> 10:34.366
THE CHRISTMAS VILLAGE
IS VERY VALUABLE.

10:34.368 --> 10:35.634
IT'S FILLED
WITH COLLECTIBLES.

10:35.636 --> 10:37.502
RUSTY, IT'S --
IT'S A SPECIAL DIORAMA

10:37.504 --> 10:39.604
MADE WITH ALL THESE MODEL
BUILDINGS FROM DICKENS NOVELS,

10:39.606 --> 10:41.773
AND THEY ALL LIGHT UP --
IT'S AWESOME.

10:41.775 --> 10:43.141
I AM SO SORRY, HONEY.

10:43.143 --> 10:46.077
I-I LEFT THE CHRISTMAS VILLAGE
IN STORAGE.

10:46.079 --> 10:47.579
WHY WOULD IT BE
IN STORAGE?

10:47.581 --> 10:50.548
WE PUT IT UP EVERY YEAR,
AND -- AND...

10:52.451 --> 10:54.085
MOM, WHERE ARE
THE PINECONE ELVES?

10:54.087 --> 10:56.154
WHAT IS THIS?
THAT LOOKS LIKE A GUILT COOKIE.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.722
THEY WERE
FALLING APART.

10:57.724 --> 11:00.291
YOU DIDN'T THROW THEM
AWAY?
I'M AFRAID I DID.

11:00.293 --> 11:02.894
YOU DUMPED HARRY,
SAM, FRANKLIN,

11:02.896 --> 11:04.262
SCOTTY, AND TWINKLE
IN THE TRASH?

11:04.264 --> 11:06.197
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU NAMED THE ELVES?

11:06.199 --> 11:07.966
MOM, THESE ARE NOT JUST
PINECONES WITH HATS.

11:07.968 --> 11:09.200
THESE ARE PART
OF MY CHILDHOOD.

11:09.202 --> 11:11.603
T-THEY'RE
A CHRISTMAS TRADITION.

11:11.605 --> 11:13.338
WELL, THIS CHRISTMAS,

11:13.340 --> 11:15.340
WE CAN MAKE
SOME NEW TRADITIONS --

11:15.342 --> 11:17.809
THE FOUR OF US,
A NEW FAMILY.

11:17.811 --> 11:20.478
LIKE ME SPENDING THE NIGHT
AT DAD'S DURING VISITS HOME?

11:20.480 --> 11:23.281
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW, I-I NEVER USED
TO DO THAT BEFORE, EITHER.

11:23.283 --> 11:25.684
WELL, YOUR FATHER
HAS MOVED BACK FROM VEGAS.

11:25.686 --> 11:27.218
HE WANTS TO BE PART
OF YOUR LIVES.

11:27.220 --> 11:28.953
I AM OFFICIALLY NEUTRAL.

11:28.955 --> 11:30.188
LIKE SWITZERLAND.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.624
YEAH, WELL,
DAD'S HOUSE IS NO CHALET,

11:32.626 --> 11:33.925
LET ME TELL YOU.

11:33.927 --> 11:36.461
IT'S -- IT'S SO MISERABLE
BEING OVER THERE IN THE MORNING.

11:36.463 --> 11:38.897
OH, LOOK,
SHE'S LEAVING AGAIN.

11:38.899 --> 11:42.133
I'M SORRY. I HAVE
TWO DEAD SANTAS IN THE MORGUE.

11:42.135 --> 11:44.302
THERE'S A NEW TRADITION
FOR YOU.

11:44.304 --> 11:47.305
OH, THIS PLACE
LOOKS SO CHRISTMASY!

11:47.307 --> 11:49.174
THANK YOU FOR WORKING
SO HARD ON IT.

11:49.176 --> 11:53.845
IT'S SO WONDERFUL HAVING
YOU ALL UNDER THE SAME ROOF.

11:53.847 --> 11:55.613
UH, OKAY...

11:55.615 --> 11:58.450
IF I'M NOT HOME
IN THE MORNING,

11:58.452 --> 12:00.785
RUSTY, ARE YOU GOOD
GETTING TO COUNTY?

12:00.787 --> 12:02.353
YEAH, NO PROBLEM.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.222
OKAY, MUAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:04.224 --> 12:07.092
LOVE YOU.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

12:07.094 --> 12:09.160
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

12:10.196 --> 12:11.463
[ Laughing ] OH, MY GOD!

12:11.465 --> 12:13.431
START TALKING.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

12:13.433 --> 12:15.033
UH...

12:15.035 --> 12:16.935
YEAH,
I-I THINK YOU'RE RIGHT.

12:16.937 --> 12:19.237
I THINK DAD'S DRINKING AGAIN,
BUT I CAN'T PROVE IT.

12:19.239 --> 12:20.805
I TOLD YOU HOW
TO PROVE IT.

12:20.807 --> 12:23.007
I DON'T WANT TO DIG THROUGH
HIS TRASH, RICKY. GOD.

12:23.009 --> 12:26.144
STAYING IN DAD'S
AWFUL APARTMENT,

12:26.146 --> 12:27.679
NO CONTRACT NEXT YEAR,

12:27.681 --> 12:29.814
AND MOM RUNNING OUT OF THE HOUSE
TO GO LOOK AT DEAD SANTAS --

12:29.816 --> 12:33.618
I MEAN, HOW HORRIBLE
DOES CHRISTMAS HAVE TO BE?

12:33.620 --> 12:35.720
LET'S TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING ELSE, OKAY?

12:35.722 --> 12:36.821
UH, W-WHAT WAS

12:36.823 --> 12:39.390
THAT ABOUT YOU GOING
TO COUNTY -- COUNTY WHAT?

12:39.392 --> 12:41.459
OH, COUNTY JAIL
TO SEE MY OTHER MOM.

12:41.461 --> 12:43.795
SHE'S DOING TIME RIGHT NOW
FOR SHOPLIFTING,

12:43.797 --> 12:46.364
BUT THE -- THE STEALING'S
MOSTLY AS A RESULT

12:46.366 --> 12:47.565
OF HER DRUG ADDICTION.

12:47.567 --> 12:50.502
ANYWAY, I-I THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE A, UM...

12:50.504 --> 12:53.238
GOOD IDEA TO GO OVER
AND CHEER HER UP A LITTLE.

12:53.240 --> 12:55.140
YOU KNOW?

12:55.142 --> 12:57.442
UM, SO, I DON'T HAVE

12:57.444 --> 12:58.877
A WHOLE LOT OF EXPERIENCE
DECORATING TREES,

12:58.879 --> 13:00.712
SO IF I PUT AN ORNAMENT
IN THE WRONG PLACE,

13:00.714 --> 13:02.080
JUST LET ME KNOW.

13:02.082 --> 13:03.648
Ricky:
NO, YOU'RE DOING FINE.

13:03.650 --> 13:06.050
RUSTY, YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
IT'S PERFECT.

13:06.052 --> 13:08.253
VERY GOOD. YEAH.

13:09.388 --> 13:11.756
Dr. Morales:
THE BEARD ON YOUR BUFF SANTA

13:11.758 --> 13:13.358
WASN'T THE ONLY THING
THAT WAS FAKE.

13:13.360 --> 13:16.661
WHEN I REMOVED THE BULLET
FROM HIS POSTERIOR,

13:16.663 --> 13:18.897
I FOUND THESE.

13:19.865 --> 13:21.199
BUTT IMPLANTS?

13:21.201 --> 13:23.535
AND THIS IS IMPORTANT
BECAUSE...?

13:23.537 --> 13:27.438
BECAUSE HE WAS SHOT IN THE
BUTTOCKS WITH A 9-MILLIMETER.

13:27.440 --> 13:29.073
2 INCHES TO THE RIGHT,

13:29.075 --> 13:32.811
AND ONE OF THESE SILICON SACKS
MIGHT'VE MADE A DIFFERENCE.

13:32.813 --> 13:34.679
BUT THE VERY WORST THING
HE COULD DO

13:34.681 --> 13:36.447
WAS SIT ON THEM
IN THE CAR.

13:36.449 --> 13:40.051
THE GRAVITY AND EXTRA PRESSURE
CAUSED HIM TO BLEED OUT.

13:40.053 --> 13:42.420
HE MIGHT'VE MADE IT
WITH A LITTLE MEDICAL ATTENTION.

13:42.422 --> 13:44.823
SO, HE DIED PARKED AROUND
THE CORNER FROM THE HOSPITAL.

13:44.825 --> 13:47.559
WHAT STOPPED HIM
FROM GOING IN?
OR WHO?

13:47.561 --> 13:50.628
WE'RE STILL NOT SURE
WHAT ROLE OUR OTHER SANTA HERE

13:50.630 --> 13:52.497
PLAYED IN THIS WHOLE THING.
[ RINGTONE PLAYING ]

13:52.499 --> 13:54.232
WELL, MAYBE THEY WERE
IN ON IT TOGETHER

13:54.234 --> 13:55.767
AND ONE SANTA
DOUBLE-CROSSED THE OTHER.

13:55.769 --> 13:57.202
WELL, IF THAT'S TRUE,
WHERE'S THE MONEY?

13:57.204 --> 13:58.837
YES, ANDY?

13:58.839 --> 14:01.639
FLYNN: We picked up Mrs. Claus
at the Beverly Hills Hotel,

14:01.641 --> 14:04.642
WHERE SHE USED A CREDIT CARD
TO COVER INCIDENTALS.

14:04.644 --> 14:07.245
WE ALSO FOUND $10,000 CASH
IN HER PURSE

14:07.247 --> 14:09.914
AND $5,000 WORTH OF PRESENTS
IN HER ROOM.

14:09.916 --> 14:11.349
WHY WERE THEY VISITING?

14:11.351 --> 14:12.884
ON VACATION
FROM NORTH DAKOTA.

14:12.886 --> 14:15.119
WE HAVEN'T NOTIFIED HER YET
BECAUSE, UH...

14:15.121 --> 14:17.822
BECAUSE OUR DANCING SANTA
WASN'T THE ONLY ONE PACKING.

14:19.491 --> 14:22.327
IT'S FOR LADIES -- GET IT? --
WITH THE PINK.

14:22.329 --> 14:23.828
AND IT'S A 9-MILLIMETER.

14:24.496 --> 14:27.365
I HAVE A RIGHT
TO BEAR ARMS.

14:27.367 --> 14:30.001
NOT WITHOUT A PERMIT,
YOU DON'T.

14:30.003 --> 14:33.538
DO YOU RECOGNIZE THIS MAN?
HIS NAME IS DEAN COKER.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.340
YOU WORK FOR ME,
YOU KNOW?

14:35.342 --> 14:39.077
I AM A TAXPAYING CITIZEN
OF THIS COUNTRY.

14:39.079 --> 14:40.745
AS ARE WE.

14:40.747 --> 14:41.646
MM-HMM.

14:41.648 --> 14:44.382
DO YOU RECOGNIZE THIS MAN?

14:44.384 --> 14:46.651
<i>I WANT TO SPEAK</i>
<i>WITH MY HUSBAND.</i>

14:46.653 --> 14:48.753
<i>IF HE WAS INVOLVED</i>
<i>IN THAT SHOOTING TODAY,</i>

14:48.755 --> 14:52.223
<i>HE WAS A HERO</i>
<i>AND NOT A CRIMINAL.</i>

14:52.225 --> 14:54.559
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK YOUR
HUSBAND'S INVOLVED, MA'AM?

14:54.561 --> 14:58.229
I'M NOT ANSWERING ANY MORE
QUESTIONS ABOUT GEORGE

14:58.231 --> 14:59.631
UNTIL I SPEAK WITH HIM.

14:59.633 --> 15:01.799
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
SHE KNOWS HE'S DEAD.

15:01.801 --> 15:04.335
<i>ANSWER SOME QUESTIONS</i>
<i>ABOUT YOURSELF, THEN.</i>
<i>OR SHE WANTS US</i>
<i>TO THINK THAT.</i>

15:04.337 --> 15:06.905
IN ADDITION TO AN UNREGISTERED
WEAPON, YOU WERE CARRYING
AROUND $10,000 IN CASH.

15:06.907 --> 15:08.506
WHERE DID YOU GET THAT MONEY,
MA'AM?

15:08.508 --> 15:11.309
I'M NOT AWARE OF ANY LAWS
AGAINST USING CASH.

15:11.311 --> 15:14.479
NO, BUT YOUR HUSBAND
JUST DANCED HIS WAY
THROUGH A BANK ROBBERY,

15:14.481 --> 15:17.248
SO WE'RE JUST CURIOUS
ABOUT ALL THE BIG BILLS.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.550
HAVE YOU NEVER HEARD OF
SHALE OIL?

15:19.552 --> 15:23.821
'CAUSE WE HAPPEN TO OWN
SEVERAL HUNDRED ACRES OF IT

15:23.823 --> 15:26.457
BACK IN TIOGA, N.D.,

15:26.459 --> 15:30.962
SO, YES, I WAS SHOPPING
WITH AMERICAN CURRENCY...

15:31.931 --> 15:35.566
...WHILE GEORGE WENT OUT AND
DID ONE OF HIS DANCE-MOB THINGS.

15:35.568 --> 15:37.702
IS HE ALWAYS ARMED
WHEN HE DANCES?

15:37.704 --> 15:40.672
OH, HE'S ARMED WHEREVER WE GO.
WE BOTH ARE.

15:40.674 --> 15:42.240
<i>YOU CAN'T DRIVE AROUND</i>
<i>THE COUNTRY</i>

15:42.242 --> 15:44.943
<i>WITH THAT MUCH MONEY</i>
<i>AND NO WAY TO PROTECT YOURSELF.</i>

15:44.945 --> 15:49.881
NOW, WHY ARE YOU BADGERING ME
ABOUT THAT GUN,

15:49.883 --> 15:52.116
AND WHERE IS MY HUSBAND?

15:54.420 --> 15:57.655
MRS. O'CONNOR,
WE'RE VERY SORRY TO INFORM YOU

15:57.657 --> 15:59.590
THAT YOUR HUSBAND WAS SHOT
BY A SECURITY GUARD

15:59.592 --> 16:02.694
DURING THE ROBBERY
OF A BANK TODAY, AND...

16:02.696 --> 16:04.829
HE DID NOT SURVIVE,
MA'AM.

16:11.303 --> 16:13.004
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT.

16:13.006 --> 16:15.740
WHAT WOULD MY HUSBAND
HAVE TO DO WITH A HOLDUP?

16:15.742 --> 16:20.812
A ROBBER TRIED TO ESCAPE.
YOUR HUSBAND INTERVENED.

16:23.582 --> 16:25.917
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

16:29.121 --> 16:31.055
G-GEORGE IS...

16:31.057 --> 16:33.157
GEORGE I-ISN'T...

16:36.061 --> 16:38.062
WHERE IS MY GEORGE?!

16:38.064 --> 16:39.664
WHO SHOT HIM?!

16:39.666 --> 16:40.865
WHO?

16:40.867 --> 16:43.001
WAS IT
THAT SON OF A BITCH?

16:43.003 --> 16:45.269
BECAUSE I-I DO KNOW HIM!

16:45.271 --> 16:47.038
I SAW HIM!

16:47.040 --> 16:48.539
WHERE DID YOU SEE HIM?

16:48.541 --> 16:50.274
AT THE REHEARSAL
FOR THE DANCE.

16:50.276 --> 16:51.776
<i>I WENT TO VIDEO IT.</i>

16:51.778 --> 16:55.480
<i>GEORGE ALWAYS WANTS ME</i>
<i>TO VIDEO THE REHEARSAL</i>

16:55.482 --> 16:56.981
SO HE CAN...

17:00.152 --> 17:01.753
SO HE...

17:03.789 --> 17:06.357
[ Voice breaking ]
SO HE CAN PRACTICE AT HOME.

17:06.359 --> 17:07.925
BUT...

17:07.927 --> 17:11.763
THIS MAN -- THIS MAN HERE,
HE TOLD ME TO STOP RECORDING.

17:11.765 --> 17:14.165
NOW, ORDINARILY, THEY ENCOURAGE
THIS KIND OF THING,

17:14.167 --> 17:17.535
BUT HE SAID THE CHOREOGRAPHER
WOULDN'T ALLOW IT.

17:17.537 --> 17:22.273
<i>MA'AM, IS THIS</i>
<i>THE CHOREOGRAPHER?</i>

17:22.275 --> 17:23.708
HER NAME'S LYDIA MANNING.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.443
YEAH.
YEAH, THAT'S HER.

17:25.445 --> 17:29.647
REAL FRIENDLY
WITH THIS BASTARD, TOO.

17:29.649 --> 17:33.551
CHOREOGRAPHER ORGANIZES
30 SANTAS AS A DIVERSION

17:33.553 --> 17:36.954
SO HER BOYFRIEND
CAN ROB A BANK.

17:36.956 --> 17:40.224
GET WARRANTS FOR LYDIA MANNING'S
CELLPHONE, COMPUTER, AND HOUSE.

17:41.794 --> 17:44.629
BUZZ, PLEASE DOCUMENT
THE SEARCH.

17:46.698 --> 17:47.999
[ DOG BARKING ]

17:48.001 --> 17:50.134
CHRISTMAS IN LAGUNA --
SOUNDS ROMANTIC.

17:50.136 --> 17:53.538
I GOT TWO ROOMS --
ONE FOR HER, ONE FOR ME.

17:53.540 --> 17:55.406
THERE IS NO ROMANCE.

17:55.408 --> 17:56.607
NO ANSWER, SIR.

17:56.609 --> 17:59.177
BUZZ, YOU'RE NOT
IN THE RESERVES YET.

17:59.179 --> 18:00.278
WAIT OVER THERE.

18:00.280 --> 18:01.412
SANCHEZ...

18:01.414 --> 18:03.881
KNOCK HARDER.

18:03.883 --> 18:05.650
L.A.P.D.!

18:07.853 --> 18:09.120
Sykes: CLEAR!

18:09.122 --> 18:11.622
UH, I GET THE FEELING
THAT WE'RE KIND OF LATE.

18:11.624 --> 18:13.458
Sanchez: CLEAR!
ALL CLEAR, SIRS!

18:13.460 --> 18:14.892
Provenza:
I GET THE FEELING

18:14.894 --> 18:20.364
THAT OUR ROBBER SANTA
AND OUR CHOREOGRAPHER

18:20.366 --> 18:21.732
WERE AN ITEM.

18:21.734 --> 18:25.169
BUZZ, GET IN HERE
AND START FILMING! LET'S GO!

18:25.171 --> 18:28.639
I WANT A CLEAR RECORD
THAT EVERYTHING IN THIS PLACE

18:28.641 --> 18:30.842
IS EXACTLY
THE WAY WE FOUND IT.

18:30.844 --> 18:34.212
I'LL BET SHE TOOK
THE 120 GRAND AND LEFT.

18:36.915 --> 18:39.283
I'VE GOT RECENT SEARCHES FOR
HOTELS IN MEXICO ON HER BROWSER.

18:39.285 --> 18:40.451
GOOD WORK.

18:40.453 --> 18:41.586
GET AHOLD
OF BORDER PATROL.

18:41.588 --> 18:42.920
Sanchez: HEY, GUYS.

18:43.722 --> 18:46.457
IN THE KITCHEN.
PLEASE BE THE MONEY.

18:46.459 --> 18:48.259
PLEASE BE THE MONEY!

18:48.261 --> 18:49.961
PLEASE BE THE MONEY.

18:51.063 --> 18:53.097
STARTER PISTOL.

18:55.400 --> 18:57.201
A BURNER PHONE.

18:57.203 --> 18:58.736
AND...

18:58.738 --> 19:01.472
SOME BATTERY-OPERATED
ELECTRONIC THING, SIR.

19:01.474 --> 19:05.176
OH, DAMN.
W-WHERE'S TAO?

19:06.845 --> 19:08.713
[ BEEP ]
STARTER PISTOL.

19:08.715 --> 19:10.281
THAT'S WEIRD.
[ BEEPING ]

19:10.283 --> 19:15.453
LAST TEXT ON THIS PHONE IS,
"OUR FRIEND IS PREPARED."

19:15.455 --> 19:16.921
WHAT FRIEND?
[ BEEP ]

19:16.923 --> 19:20.358
YOU KNOW, I THINK THIS IS
THE FREQUENCY JAMMER.

19:20.360 --> 19:21.526
HEY, DETECTIVE.

19:21.528 --> 19:23.027
YOU MISSED SOMETHING
IN THE TRASH.

19:23.029 --> 19:24.629
HOW DO YOU TURN
THIS THING OFF?

19:24.631 --> 19:26.998
OH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I THINK IT'S THE --

19:34.273 --> 19:36.140
DYE PACKS.

19:45.250 --> 19:49.120
WELL, IF NOTHING ELSE,
THE DYE PACKS IN HER TRASH

19:49.122 --> 19:53.224
SUGGEST THAT DEAN AND LYDIA
MET UP AFTER THE ROBBERY.

19:53.226 --> 19:56.060
AND THAT MAYBE SHE LEFT HIM
BLEEDING TO DEATH IN HIS CAR.

19:56.062 --> 19:59.030
SO SHE'S EITHER COLD-BLOODED
OR IN A COMPLETE PANIC.

19:59.032 --> 20:01.399
AND WE WON'T KNOW
WHICH UNTIL WE FIND HER.

20:01.401 --> 20:04.869
WELL, MAYBE LYDIA
HASN'T MADE IT TO MEXICO YET.

20:04.871 --> 20:09.106
SYKES: What if, instead of
driving over the border,

20:09.108 --> 20:10.274
SHE TOOK A FLIGHT?

20:10.276 --> 20:12.610
THE COMPUTER SEARCH
COULD'VE BEEN A MISDIRECT.

20:12.612 --> 20:14.212
WELL, SHE'D HAVE TO USE
A FAKE I.D.

20:14.214 --> 20:17.949
WITH THAT MUCH CASH,
FLYING'S RISKY. [ LAUGHS ]

20:17.951 --> 20:20.885
TELLING YOU, THAT MONEY IS
MORE WELL-TRAVELED THAN <i>I</i> AM.

20:20.887 --> 20:25.056
WAIT. IF THE DYE PACKS
WENT OFF IN THE TRASH,
THEY WERE STILL ARMED.

20:25.058 --> 20:28.893
Yeah, yeah,
which means the robbers

20:28.895 --> 20:31.495
BLOCKED THE RADIO SIGNAL
AT THE BANK DOOR.

20:31.497 --> 20:33.564
THAT'S WHAT <i>I</i> SAID
AT THE CRIME SCENE,

20:33.566 --> 20:35.566
BUT YOU SAID --
YEAH, YEAH.

20:35.568 --> 20:38.469
TAO, UH, HOW COULD
OUR ROBBER SANTA

20:38.471 --> 20:39.837
HAVE GOTTEN AWAY
WITH THAT?

20:39.839 --> 20:42.206
HAD TO KNOW WHICH [LAUGHS]
FREQUENCY TO BLOCK.

20:43.809 --> 20:46.043
THE LAST TEXT
ON LYDIA'S PHONE

20:46.045 --> 20:49.213
indicates that they had
an accomplice inside the bank.

20:49.215 --> 20:51.983
OKAY, WE NEED TO REVIEW
ALL OF THE FINANCES

20:51.985 --> 20:53.551
OF EVERYBODY WORKING THERE.

20:53.553 --> 20:54.919
THIS ISN'T JUST A ROBBERY.

20:54.921 --> 20:57.288
THIS IS A DOUBLE CASE
OF FELONY SANTACIDE.

20:57.290 --> 20:58.356
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

20:58.358 --> 21:00.124
I'M SO SORRY.

21:00.126 --> 21:01.993
I KEEP THINKING
WE'RE DONE,

21:01.995 --> 21:03.894
BUT NOW IT LOOKS LIKE
OUR CHRISTMAS EVE PARTY

21:03.896 --> 21:05.529
MAY NOT HAPPEN.
IT'S ALL RIGHT, MOM.

21:05.531 --> 21:07.898
UH, WE'LL KEEP GOING,
JUST IN CASE.

21:07.900 --> 21:09.734
I WILL CALL YOU
IF I'M GONNA BE LATE.
Ricky: OKAY.

21:09.736 --> 21:11.535
DON'T WORRY.

21:11.537 --> 21:12.803
BYE, MOM!

21:12.805 --> 21:14.038
BYE!
BYE!

21:14.040 --> 21:16.874
[ DOOR OPENS ]
[ SIGHS ]

21:16.876 --> 21:19.543
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
DID THOSE WINE BOTTLES
COME OUT OF JACK'S GARBAGE?

21:19.545 --> 21:22.747
YEAH, JUST DON'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT THAT TO MOM.

21:22.749 --> 21:25.449
BUT WHAT IF SHE FINDS OUT WE
KNEW AND DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING?

21:25.451 --> 21:28.019
HERE'S ANOTHER CHRISTMAS
TRADITION YOU NEED TO LEARN.

21:28.021 --> 21:30.154
Ricky: RIGHT, OKAY,
SO, AFTER A CERTAIN AGE,

21:30.156 --> 21:32.556
THE HOLIDAYS ARE
FOR OUR PARENTS, NOT FOR US,

21:32.558 --> 21:34.625
SO IT'S OUR JOB,

21:34.627 --> 21:37.228
OUR RESPONSIBILITY,
REALLY,

21:37.230 --> 21:38.863
TO MAKE THEM FEEL LIKE
WE'RE HAVING

21:38.865 --> 21:40.498
AS GREAT A TIME
AS WE DID WHEN WE WERE 7.

21:40.500 --> 21:43.901
SO, I-IS THAT WHY YOU WERE
LOOKING SO HARD

21:43.903 --> 21:46.604
FOR HARRY, SAM,
FRANKLIN, SCOTTY, AND...

21:46.606 --> 21:47.938
TWINKLE.
...TWINKLE?

21:47.940 --> 21:51.042
RUSTY, HE'S OUR FATHER,
SO IT'S OUR SECRET.

21:51.044 --> 21:54.712
WHY RUIN CHRISTMAS BY TELLING
HER DAD DROPPED OUT OF A.A.?

21:54.714 --> 21:58.282
I HAVE NOTHING TO
CONFESS BECAUSE I HAD
NOTHING TO DO WITH IT!

21:58.284 --> 21:59.984
Tao:
SO, IT'S JUST A COINCIDENCE

21:59.986 --> 22:01.585
YOU STARTED WORKING AT
McCORMICK SAVINGS SIX WEEKS

22:01.587 --> 22:04.455
BEFORE THEIR FIRST ATTEMPTED
ROBBERY IN OVER A DECADE?

22:04.457 --> 22:08.192
FAITH, WE LOOKED INTO
YOUR CREDIT REPORT.

22:08.194 --> 22:13.130
YOU HAVE $26,000 IN DEBT
AT U.S. BANK,

22:13.132 --> 22:15.232
$4,500
AT FIRST REPUBLIC.

22:15.234 --> 22:17.301
AND THEN THERE'S THE FLIGHT
YOU BOOKED TO VANCOUVER.

22:17.303 --> 22:18.369
I-I CAN EXPLAIN THAT!

22:18.371 --> 22:19.970
A ONE-WAY FLIGHT
LEAVING TONIGHT?

22:19.972 --> 22:22.206
OKAY! O-OKAY,
JUST GIVE ME A CHANCE.

22:22.208 --> 22:24.909
<i>I HAVE</i>
<i>AN ONLINE-SHOPPING PROBLEM,</i>

22:24.911 --> 22:27.578
<i>AND I TOOK THIS JOB TO HELP</i>
<i>KEEP ME OFF MY COMPUTER...</i>
<i>WHAT DID WE FIND</i>
<i>AT HER HOUSE?</i>

22:27.580 --> 22:30.214
THE SUITCASE IS PACKED
FOR CANADA, MA'AM.
<i>...DURING THE HOLIDAYS,</i>
<i>WHICH IS REALLY IMPORTANT...</i>

22:30.216 --> 22:31.982
BUT NO MONEY.
<i>...TO SOMEONE WITH MY PROBLEM.</i>

22:31.984 --> 22:35.219
OH, GREAT!
AND I-I-I'M NOT
FLEEING THE COUNTRY!

22:35.221 --> 22:37.521
I'M...I'M...

22:37.523 --> 22:38.723
I'M CANADIAN.

22:38.725 --> 22:40.091
AND MY PARENTS
BOUGHT ME A CAR

22:40.093 --> 22:42.093
FOR CHRISTMAS
BECAUSE I CAN'T AFFORD ONE,

22:42.095 --> 22:45.663
SO I'M FLYING TO VANCOUVER FOR
THE HOLIDAYS AND DRIVING BACK.

22:45.665 --> 22:47.898
OKAY,
WE'LL CHECK ON THAT.

22:47.900 --> 22:50.034
TELL US ONE MORE THING.

22:50.036 --> 22:52.503
WHERE IS LYDIA MANNING?

22:54.272 --> 22:57.274
I-I HAVE NO IDEA
WHO THAT IS.
COME ON, FAITH.

22:57.276 --> 22:59.777
I-I SWEAR I'VE NEVER --
I'VE NEVER SEEN HER BEFORE!

22:59.779 --> 23:01.912
I DIDN'T EVEN
WANT TO WORK YESTERDAY!

23:01.914 --> 23:05.816
<i>THE SCHEDULE CHANGED, AND</i>
<i>I WAS TOLD THAT I'D BE FIRED</i>

23:05.818 --> 23:07.251
<i>UNLESS I SHOWED UP.</i>

23:07.253 --> 23:09.854
<i>I HAD TO SWITCH MY FLIGHT</i>
<i>AND EVERYTHING.</i>

23:09.856 --> 23:11.188
WHO WOULDN'T GIVE YOU
THE DAY OFF?

23:11.190 --> 23:13.057
MEL --
SHE MADE ME COME IN,

23:13.059 --> 23:15.159
EVEN THOUGH I FOUND SOMEONE
TO COVER MY SHIFT.

23:15.161 --> 23:17.928
Tao: MEL -- WHO CAME
IN WITH YOU YESTERDAY?

23:17.930 --> 23:19.597
MEL,
YOUR ASSISTANT MANAGER?

23:19.599 --> 23:22.733
<i>YES. AND THEN SHE PUT ME</i>
<i>ON THE BUSINESS LINE.</i>

23:22.735 --> 23:25.870
Tao: OUR TELLER, FAITH, HAS
PLENTY OF REASONS TO ROB A BANK,

23:25.872 --> 23:27.872
NOT SO FOR HER BOSS.

23:27.874 --> 23:30.141
MELANIE JORDAN
IS A LONGTIME EMPLOYEE.

23:30.143 --> 23:33.244
SHE'S MARRIED. SHE'S GOT A KID.
NO FINANCIAL PROBLEMS.

23:33.246 --> 23:36.280
ALSO, NO EVIDENCE
OF HER BUYING BURNER PHONES,

23:36.282 --> 23:38.182
A STARTER PISTOL,
SANTA SUITS,

23:38.184 --> 23:40.384
OR ANYTHING ELSE
CONNECTED TO THIS ROBBERY.

23:40.386 --> 23:42.853
WELL, MAYBE SHE OWES MONEY
TO THE KIND OF PEOPLE

23:42.855 --> 23:44.422
THAT DON'T DO BUSINESS
ON PAPER.

23:44.424 --> 23:48.325
SHE ALSO WOULD PROBABLY KNOW
THE FREQUENCY TO THE DYE PACKS.

23:48.327 --> 23:49.860
Sanchez: THIS WAY.

23:52.364 --> 23:54.231
HEY, I'M SORRY
TO BRING MY SON.

23:54.233 --> 23:57.635
I CALLED MY REGULAR SITTER,
BUT SINCE IT'S CHRISTMAS EVE...

23:57.637 --> 23:58.836
OH, I UNDERSTAND.

23:58.838 --> 24:00.838
THANK YOU
FOR COMING BACK DOWN.

24:00.840 --> 24:02.239
OH, I'M HAPPY TO HELP.

24:02.241 --> 24:05.676
BUT KEVIN HAS A BIG
CHRISTMAS RECITAL TOMORROW

24:05.678 --> 24:07.144
AT THE CATHEDRAL
DOWNTOWN.

24:07.146 --> 24:08.946
IS THERE SOMEWHERE HE COULD GO
TO PRACTICE WHILE WE TALK?

24:08.948 --> 24:10.514
I'LL JUST HELP HIM
SET UP.

24:10.516 --> 24:11.982
CERTAINLY.
DETECTIVE.

24:11.984 --> 24:15.886
ALL RIGHT, KEVIN,
LET'S HEAR WHAT YOU GOT.

24:22.494 --> 24:24.728
SHE CLEARLY
WAS NOT ON THE RUN.

24:24.730 --> 24:27.731
NO, BUT WHEN WE GOT TO
HER HOUSE, SHE WAS JUST
GETTING OUT OF A CAB.

24:27.733 --> 24:29.800
REALLY?
COMING FROM WHERE?

24:29.802 --> 24:31.235
CABBY SAID UNION STATION.

24:31.237 --> 24:33.471
MEL TOLD US
SHE WAS DROPPING OFF A FRIEND,

24:33.473 --> 24:35.105
CLAIMED SHE WAS HAVING
CAR TROUBLE.

24:35.107 --> 24:36.807
WAS HER SON
IN THE CAB WITH HER?

24:36.809 --> 24:38.509
YEAH,
THAT'S THE WEIRD THING.

24:38.511 --> 24:40.744
KEVIN WAS SITTING ALONE
IN THE LIVING ROOM, PRACTICING.

24:40.746 --> 24:43.347
SHOULD WE GET A WARRANT
FOR HER HOUSE?
Provenza:
ON WHAT GROUNDS?

24:43.349 --> 24:46.083
"WOMAN GOES TO
THE TRAIN STATION IN A CAB

24:46.085 --> 24:47.785
WHILE HER SON
PLAYS HIS CELLO?"

24:47.787 --> 24:50.855
NOT EXACTLY THE SMOKING GUN
WE'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR.

24:50.857 --> 24:51.989
NO, IT ISN'T.

24:51.991 --> 24:53.624
MIKE,
LET'S GET BUZZ TO GRAB

24:53.626 --> 24:56.760
THIS AFTERNOON'S SECURITY
FOOTAGE FROM UNION STATION.

24:56.762 --> 25:00.231
MAYBE THE FRIEND SHE DROPPED OFF
IS OUR CHOREOGRAPHER.

25:00.233 --> 25:03.834
HOPEFULLY,
WITH A SUITCASE FULL OF CASH.

25:03.836 --> 25:07.304
AND A SMOKING GUN.

25:12.110 --> 25:15.613
[ SLOW-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

25:35.467 --> 25:37.034
YOU'RE REALLY AMAZING.

25:37.036 --> 25:38.068
[ GASPS ]

25:38.070 --> 25:39.904
SORRY.
NO. THANK YOU.

25:39.906 --> 25:41.272
I, UH...

25:41.274 --> 25:43.474
I FEEL LIKE
I STILL HAVE THE RIGHT MOVES.

25:43.476 --> 25:44.742
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:44.744 --> 25:45.776
WHERE'S RICKY?

25:45.778 --> 25:47.778
OH, HE RAN OUT SOMEWHERE.

25:47.780 --> 25:49.747
HE SAID IT'S A SURPRISE.

25:49.749 --> 25:51.482
IS THE PARTY GONNA HAPPEN?

25:51.484 --> 25:52.816
MAYBE.

25:52.818 --> 25:55.419
UH, BUT IT MIGHT BE
A LITTLE LATER THAN WE PLANNED.

25:55.421 --> 25:57.488
SHARON HAS HER PRIORITIES,
YOU KNOW?

25:57.490 --> 25:58.422
RIGHT.

25:58.424 --> 26:00.791
OH, UH,
HOW WAS YOUR VISIT

26:00.793 --> 26:02.026
WITH
YOUR BIOLOGICAL MOM?

26:02.028 --> 26:03.661
UH, WELL...

26:03.663 --> 26:05.663
COUNTY JAIL AT CHRISTMAS...
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:05.665 --> 26:08.032
...ABOUT AS FUN
AS IT SOUNDS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:08.034 --> 26:11.035
BUT, YOU KNOW,
IT KEEPS US FROM PRETENDING

26:11.037 --> 26:14.705
LIKE MY MOM HAS NO PROBLEMS
WITH DRUGS OR ALCOHOL.

26:15.874 --> 26:17.408
OH, MY GOD.

26:19.578 --> 26:22.379
WHY IS OUR NOT TELLING MOTHER
BOTHERING YOU SO MUCH?

26:22.381 --> 26:25.416
WELL, BECAUSE I FEEL LIKE
IF SHE FINDS OUT

26:25.418 --> 26:27.251
WE'RE HOLDING BACK
THAT KIND OF INFORMATION,

26:27.253 --> 26:29.987
IT -- IT -- IT'S REALLY
GONNA HURT HER FEELINGS.

26:29.989 --> 26:32.790
I MEAN, LOOK,
I-I-I LIVE HERE.

26:32.792 --> 26:35.693
I'M WITH SHARON ALL THE TIME.
SHE    <i>C</i>HANDLE THIS.

26:36.962 --> 26:38.562
I'M JUST, UH...

26:38.564 --> 26:41.565
I'M WORRIED [SIGHS] T-THAT DAD'S
GONNA SAY HE'S DRINKING

26:41.567 --> 26:45.269
BECAUSE, YOU KNOW, HE -- HE
FEELS LIKE HE TRIED TO CHANGE,

26:45.271 --> 26:47.137
A-AND WE STILL CUT HIM
OUT OF CHRISTMAS.

26:47.139 --> 26:48.872
YEAH, AND HE PROBABLY
WILL SAY THAT

26:48.874 --> 26:50.374
BECAUSE USERS
ALWAYS FIND A REASON

26:50.376 --> 26:52.676
WHY IT'S SOMEONE ELSE'S FAULT
THEY'RE DRINKING,

26:52.678 --> 26:54.111
AND SHARON KNOWS THAT.

26:54.113 --> 26:56.547
YOU JUST -- YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND
THE WHOLE HISTORY.

26:56.549 --> 27:00.050
MOM PROMISED DAD THAT HE
WOULD NEVER SEE HIS KIDS AGAIN

27:00.052 --> 27:01.418
UNLESS HE STAYED SOBER,

27:01.420 --> 27:03.954
AND, YOU KNOW,
YOU MAY NOT KNOW THIS,

27:03.956 --> 27:06.090
BUT, UM,
SHE KEEPS HER PROMISES.

27:06.092 --> 27:07.891
RIGHT.

27:07.893 --> 27:09.627
[ SIGHS ]

27:09.629 --> 27:10.828
WELL...

27:10.830 --> 27:14.632
YOU MAY HAVE TO PRETEND
LIKE YOU'RE 7 AT CHRISTMAS,

27:14.634 --> 27:16.767
BUT YOU AND RICKY
ARE STILL ADULTS.

27:16.769 --> 27:20.037
DOES SHARON STILL TELL YOU
WHO YOU CAN AND CAN'T SEE?

27:20.039 --> 27:21.438
'CAUSE SHE DOESN'T DO THAT
TO ME.

27:21.440 --> 27:24.775
DON'T YOU THINK THIS MIGHT BE
WHAT JACK WANTS --

27:24.777 --> 27:26.377
FOR YOU
TO NOT TRUST SHARON?

27:26.379 --> 27:28.479
[ CELLO PLAYS
"WHAT CHILD IS THIS" ]

27:28.481 --> 27:31.115
[ SIGHS ]

27:34.552 --> 27:36.987
WE FOUND THE CHOREOGRAPHER'S CAR
AT UNION STATION

27:36.989 --> 27:39.890
PARKED SIDEWAYS IN
A HANDICAP SPOT RIGHT IN FRONT.

27:39.892 --> 27:41.659
NO MONEY IN THE CIVIC

27:41.661 --> 27:44.228
AND NOTHING TO POINT US
TO LYDIA'S WHEREABOUTS,

27:44.230 --> 27:46.330
BUT AMTRAK POLICE
AND METROLINK SECURITY

27:46.332 --> 27:49.700
ARE DISTRIBUTING LYDIA'S PICTURE
TO ALL THEIR CONDUCTORS.

27:49.702 --> 27:52.870
Flynn: SO, CELLO BOY'S MOM
GOES TO THE TRAIN STATION

27:52.872 --> 27:55.305
WHERE THE WOMAN WHO ROBBED
HER BANK DUMPED HER CAR?

27:55.307 --> 27:56.807
IT IS JUST A COINCIDENCE

27:56.809 --> 27:59.777
UNTIL WE CAN PLACE
THE TWO OF THEM THERE TOGETHER.

27:59.779 --> 28:03.280
WHERE IS THE UNION STATION
SURVEILLANCE VIDEO, BUZZ?

28:03.282 --> 28:05.315
UH, STILL UPLOADING IT,
CAPTAIN.

28:05.317 --> 28:07.451
Patrice: UH, LOUIE?

28:07.453 --> 28:08.686
OH.

28:09.454 --> 28:12.723
MRS. PERRY,
HOW LOVELY TO SEE YOU.

28:12.725 --> 28:14.658
THANK YOU.
IS THERE SOMETHING
WE CAN DO FOR YOU?

28:14.660 --> 28:17.361
OH, NO, NO.
I'M HERE BECAUSE --

28:17.363 --> 28:20.030
UH [CLEARS THROAT]
YOU ALL REMEMBER, UH, PATRICE.

28:20.032 --> 28:21.932
UH, SHE'S JUST GOING
TO STICK AROUND

28:21.934 --> 28:23.333
WHILE WE, UH,
WRAP UP HERE.

28:23.335 --> 28:24.735
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

28:24.737 --> 28:27.037
AND THEN WE'RE LEAVING
FOR LAGUNA.

28:27.039 --> 28:28.572
OR I CAN WAIT
DOWNSTAIRS.

28:28.574 --> 28:30.407
OH, NO, NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO.

28:30.409 --> 28:33.544
UH, W-WE JUST HAVE TO, UH,
FIND MONEY FROM A ROBBERY

28:33.546 --> 28:36.714
AND GET A CONFESSION
AND THEN FILL OUT SOME PAPERWORK

28:36.716 --> 28:41.552
FOR A COUPLE OF FELONY MURDERS
INVOLVING A SANTA FLASH MOB.

28:41.554 --> 28:43.020
UH, AND THEN
WE'RE DONE.

28:43.022 --> 28:46.523
AND -- AND, UH, WE,
LIEUTENANT AND I, ARE GOING TO,

28:46.525 --> 28:49.560
UH, INTERVIEW A SUSPECT
RIGHT NOW.

28:49.562 --> 28:51.128
SO...

28:51.130 --> 28:52.763
UH, OH.

28:52.765 --> 28:55.099
UH, WAIT, UH,
HERE'S MY CROSSWORD PUZZLE.

28:55.101 --> 28:56.333
HERE.

28:56.335 --> 28:59.770
I'M, UH -- I'M REALLY STUCK
ON 12 ACROSS.

29:05.477 --> 29:07.878
Sharon: SHE WAS THE
CHOREOGRAPHER OF THE FLASH MOB.

29:07.880 --> 29:10.114
NO, I DON'T KNOW HER.

29:11.015 --> 29:14.685
YOU DIDN'T GO TO THE
TRAIN STATION WITH HER TODAY?

29:14.687 --> 29:15.519
WHAT? NO.

29:15.521 --> 29:17.621
I HAD A FRIEND IN TOWN,

29:17.623 --> 29:19.623
AND I TOLD YOU,
I'M HAVING CAR TROUBLE.

29:19.625 --> 29:21.959
ARE YOU SAYING -- WAS THIS WOMAN
INVOLVED IN THE ROBBERY?

29:21.961 --> 29:24.661
WHO IS THE FRIEND THAT
YOU DROVE TO THE TRAIN STATION?

29:24.663 --> 29:25.963
I NEED A NAME.

29:25.965 --> 29:29.733
LOOK, MS. JORDAN, IT MAY TAKE US
THE REST OF THE NIGHT,

29:29.735 --> 29:32.069
BUT WE WILL FIND
SURVEILLANCE VIDEO

29:32.071 --> 29:33.937
OF YOU SITTING
IN THIS WOMAN'S CAR

29:33.939 --> 29:37.241
<i>AT THE TRAIN STATION,</i>
<i>AND WHEN WE DO...</i>

29:37.243 --> 29:38.509
YOU'RE GOING
TO BE CHARGED WITH MURDER.

29:38.511 --> 29:40.577
NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

29:40.579 --> 29:42.079
NO.

29:42.081 --> 29:43.280
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

29:43.282 --> 29:44.782
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:44.784 --> 29:46.917
THEY FORCED ME TO DO IT.

29:47.519 --> 29:49.253
<i>THEY THREATENED MY SON.</i>

29:49.255 --> 29:50.654
OH, HERE WE GO.

29:50.656 --> 29:52.723
<i>WHO FORCED YOU?</i>
<i>THIS WOMAN, LYDIA,</i>

29:52.725 --> 29:54.124
AND HER BOYFRIEND --
THEY THREATENED ME!

29:54.126 --> 29:55.793
I MEAN,
WHAT WAS I SUPPOSED TO DO?

29:55.795 --> 29:59.062
I THOUGHT AFTER THE ROBBERY,
IT'D BE OVER,

29:59.064 --> 30:01.632
BUT THEN LYDIA
CAME TO MY HOUSE.

30:01.634 --> 30:04.434
LYDIA CAME
TO YOUR HOUSE TODAY?
YEAH.

30:04.436 --> 30:07.070
SHE'S FREAKING OUT BECAUSE
HER BOYFRIEND GOT KILLED,

30:07.072 --> 30:09.740
AND SHE WANTED TO STASH
THE MONEY WITH ME, AND
I BEGGED HER NOT TO.

30:09.742 --> 30:12.042
I TOLD HER I COULD JUST
TAKE THE MONEY BACK TO THE BANK,

30:12.044 --> 30:14.545
AND IT WOULD ALL BE OVER,
AND THEN SHE PULLED OUT A GUN!

30:14.547 --> 30:18.215
I MEAN, MY CHILD [SNIFFLES]
WAS IN THE HOUSE.

30:18.217 --> 30:19.583
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

30:19.585 --> 30:21.718
SO, SHE --
SHE TOOK THE MONEY

30:21.720 --> 30:24.221
AND THEN SHE MADE ME
DRIVE HER TO UNION STATION,

30:24.223 --> 30:27.124
AND AS WE'RE PULLING UP,
SHE JUST JUMPS OUT OF THE CAR.

30:27.126 --> 30:29.726
SO, YEAH,
I WAS AT UNION STATION,

30:29.728 --> 30:31.929
BUT I JUST --
I LEFT HER CAR THERE,

30:31.931 --> 30:34.398
AND I GOT HOME TO MY CHILD
AS FAST AS I COULD.

30:34.400 --> 30:35.699
OH, MY GOD!

30:35.701 --> 30:37.467
WHERE WAS SHE GOING --
LYDIA?

30:37.469 --> 30:38.969
I DON'T KNOW.
I WAS JUST --

30:38.971 --> 30:40.571
I WAS JUST GRATEFUL
THAT I MADE IT HOME ALIVE.

30:40.573 --> 30:42.773
I'M STILL SHAKING.
OKAY, OKAY.

30:42.775 --> 30:45.509
WHEN DID LYDIA AND HER BOYFRIEND
FIRST CONTACT YOU?

30:45.511 --> 30:48.312
[ SIGHS ]
TWO WEEKS AGO.

30:48.314 --> 30:51.381
THEY KNEW ALL OF THESE THINGS
ABOUT KEVIN --

30:51.383 --> 30:53.450
WHERE HE WENT TO SCHOOL,

30:53.452 --> 30:56.186
WHAT TIME WE WENT TO BED
AT NIGHT.

30:56.188 --> 30:57.588
AND KEVIN'S FATHER AND I
WERE SEPARATED,

30:57.590 --> 30:59.356
AND WE LIVE ALONE,
SO I WAS SCARED TO DEATH.

31:00.058 --> 31:04.795
SO, I TOLD THEM EVERYTHING
THAT THEY ASKED ABOUT THE BANK.

31:04.797 --> 31:07.965
<i>WHAT LINE WOULD BE CASH</i>
<i>HEAVY, WHAT FREQUENCY WAS</i>
<i>TIED TO THE DYE PACKS.</i>

31:07.967 --> 31:10.500
SHE'S GOT A LOT
OF GOOD ANSWERS.
<i>I MEAN, THE WHOLE THING,</i>
<i>ALL I WAS TRYING TO DO</i>

31:10.502 --> 31:12.636
AND WE WON'T KNOW IF ANY OF THEM
ARE TRUE UNTIL WE FIND LYDIA.
<i>...WAS PROTECT MY SON.</i>

31:12.638 --> 31:14.438
Buzz: YEAH,
AND THAT MAY TAKE A WHILE.
<i>THAT'S EVERYTHING I KNOW.</i>

31:14.440 --> 31:17.274
I JUST FINISHED UPLOADING
120 CAMERAS' WORTH

31:17.276 --> 31:18.809
OF SECURITY FOOTAGE
FROM UNION STATION.
<i>I NEED A LAWYER.</i>

31:18.811 --> 31:20.878
I'VE GOT IT SYNCHED
TO THE TIME WHEN --

31:20.880 --> 31:24.014
OH, HOLY NIGHT.
WAIT A MINUTE.

31:24.016 --> 31:25.749
LOOK, IT'S HER --

31:25.751 --> 31:28.752
OUR ASSISTANT BANK MANAGER
IN LYDIA'S VEHICLE.

31:28.754 --> 31:30.921
WE HAVE THE CAR
AND THE SUSPECT.

31:30.923 --> 31:33.323
OKAY, WE FOUND A SHOT

31:33.325 --> 31:37.261
OF MEL PARKING LYDIA MANNING'S
RED CIVIC AT THE TRAIN STATION.

31:37.263 --> 31:38.562
BUT SHE WAS ALONE,
JUST LIKE SHE SAID.

31:38.564 --> 31:39.963
Sharon: SO,
UNTIL WE GET SOME WORD

31:39.965 --> 31:43.367
FROM BORDER PATROL OR AMTRAK
ON LYDIA'S WHEREABOUTS,

31:43.369 --> 31:44.868
WE ARE STUCK.

31:44.870 --> 31:46.904
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

31:50.909 --> 31:53.710
BEFORE WE THROW IN THE TOWEL,
THOUGH,

31:53.712 --> 31:55.913
WE'LL HAVE A LITTLE CHAT
WITH KEVIN.

31:55.915 --> 31:58.849
AND I THINK WE SHOULD RECORD
THAT CHAT.

31:58.851 --> 32:00.250
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

32:00.252 --> 32:02.853
[  <i>POLICE RADIO CHATTER</i>]

32:02.855 --> 32:04.288
<i>HEY, KEVIN.</i>

32:04.290 --> 32:06.523
<i>YOU'VE BEEN PRACTICING</i>
<i>FOR SO LONG.</i>

32:06.525 --> 32:08.458
WOULD YOU LIKE A COOKIE?

32:12.196 --> 32:15.232
[ SIGHS ]
NO, I'M ON A DIET.

32:15.234 --> 32:19.403
MOM AND DEAN ARE TRYING
TO GET ME TO BE "THE NEW KEVIN."

32:19.405 --> 32:22.005
DEAN?
WHO'S DEAN?

32:22.007 --> 32:24.541
OH, DEAN'S MY TRAINER.

32:24.543 --> 32:26.677
I CALL HIM "MEAN DEAN"
SOMETIMES.

32:26.679 --> 32:28.712
DON'T TELL MY MOM THAT.
Sanchez:
WE WON'T TELL HER.

32:28.714 --> 32:30.881
WE WON'T TELL HER IF YOU
HAVE A COOKIE, EITHER.

32:30.883 --> 32:32.382
IT'S CHRISTMAS.

32:34.886 --> 32:39.423
Provenza: I MEAN, WHAT KIND
OF MOTHER HIRES A TRAINER

32:39.425 --> 32:40.824
FOR THEIR 9-YEAR-OLD?

32:40.826 --> 32:43.360
THE KIND WHO USES SANTA
TO ROB HER OWN BANK.

32:43.362 --> 32:47.030
SO, WHY DO YOU NEED
TO BE THE NEW KEVIN?

32:47.032 --> 32:48.832
YOU SEEM GREAT TO ME.

32:48.834 --> 32:52.769
WELL, IN JANUARY, I'M MOVING
TO THE MYER'S SCHOOL FOR BOYS.

32:52.771 --> 32:54.871
I'LL HAVE TO MAKE
NEW FRIENDS.

32:54.873 --> 32:57.507
<i>IT'S NEVER EASY BEING THE NEW</i>
<i>KID WHO PLAYS THE CELLO.</i>
<i>MYER'S SCHOOL FOR BOYS.</i>

32:57.509 --> 33:00.477
HUH! LOOK AT THIS PLACE.
IT'S LIKE HOGWARTS.
<i>WOW.</i>
<i>THAT IS A BIG CHANGE.</i>

33:00.479 --> 33:01.979
<i>YEAH.</i>

33:01.981 --> 33:03.080
40 GRAND A YEAR TUITION.

33:03.082 --> 33:04.648
<i>I DIDN'T THINK</i>
<i>I WAS GONNA GET IN,</i>

33:04.650 --> 33:06.583
BUT IT'S HAPPENING.

33:06.585 --> 33:08.752
MY MOM WENT TO
MY OLD SCHOOL TODAY

33:08.754 --> 33:10.687
TO CLEAN OUT
MY MUSIC LOCKER.

33:10.689 --> 33:12.889
SHE WENT TO
YOUR OLD SCHOOL TODAY?

33:12.891 --> 33:14.624
THEY'RE OPEN
DURING CHRISTMAS?

33:14.626 --> 33:16.994
NO, MOM'S
THE ORCHESTRA SPONSOR.

33:16.996 --> 33:18.996
SHE HAS A KEY.

33:19.764 --> 33:21.565
WHICH PUBLIC SCHOOL
DO YOU GO TO, KEVIN?

33:21.567 --> 33:22.766
NORRIS ELEMENTARY.

33:22.768 --> 33:24.901
TAO, GO, GO --
LIGHTS AND SIRENS.

33:24.903 --> 33:27.404
BUZZ, GO.
FILM EVERYTHING.

33:27.406 --> 33:28.939
I-IF YOU FIND
THAT MONEY,

33:28.941 --> 33:31.141
I WILL PERSONALLY PAY
FOR YOUR DERMABRASION.

33:31.143 --> 33:34.478
AND NO WARRANTS!
EXIGENT CIRCUMSTANCES!

33:34.480 --> 33:36.713
I'M ABOUT TO LOSE
MY CHRISTMAS RESERVATIONS.

33:36.715 --> 33:39.016
<i>YOU'VE BEEN VERY HELPFUL.</i>
<i>THANK YOU.</i>

33:41.619 --> 33:44.521
UH, COULD I MAYBE
HAVE A...

33:44.523 --> 33:46.356
ANOTHER COOKIE?

33:46.358 --> 33:48.492
HAVE THE WHOLE PLATE,
KID.

33:58.436 --> 34:00.103
Provenza:
THE GOOD NEWS IS,

34:00.105 --> 34:04.674
WE FOUND ENOUGH MONEY FOR YOU
TO PAY TUITION FOR THREE YEARS

34:04.676 --> 34:06.076
TO MYER'S SCHOOL FOR BOYS,

34:06.078 --> 34:08.812
WHICH NEITHER YOU
OR YOUR HUSBAND COULD AFFORD.

34:08.814 --> 34:11.014
THE BAD NEWS IS,
WE FOUND IT

34:11.016 --> 34:14.818
IN AN ELEMENTARY-SCHOOL LOCKER
OF YOUR CLIENT'S SON.

34:14.820 --> 34:18.989
NOW, IT'S BETTER THAN THE
THIRD THAT SHE WOULD'VE GOTTEN

34:18.991 --> 34:21.591
IF SHE'D HAD TO SPLIT THE MONEY
WITH HER ACCOMPLICES.

34:21.593 --> 34:23.060
ON THE OTHER HAND,

34:23.062 --> 34:25.362
THE DEATH OF TWO SANTAS
COUNTS AS FELONY MURDER

34:25.364 --> 34:28.965
BECAUSE THEY DIED AS
A DIRECT RESULT OF HER ACTIONS.

34:28.967 --> 34:32.569
NOW, THAT'S PRETTY BAD, BUT
THE DEATH OF LYDIA MANNING...

34:32.571 --> 34:34.071
OH, WELL,
THAT'S FIRST-DEGREE MURDER.

34:34.073 --> 34:35.138
AH.
Mel: LYDIA?

34:35.140 --> 34:36.606
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
I KILLED LYDIA?

34:36.608 --> 34:38.775
H-HOLD ON.
DON'T -- DON'T TALK.

34:39.477 --> 34:41.144
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

34:41.146 --> 34:42.813
SO, WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
SHE KILLED LYDIA?

34:42.815 --> 34:44.681
Sharon:
AFTER WE FOUND THE MONEY,

34:44.683 --> 34:46.850
WE SENT A TEAM
OF PATROL OFFICERS

34:46.852 --> 34:49.286
WHO THOROUGHLY SEARCHED
YOUR HOUSE, MS. JORDAN,

34:49.288 --> 34:53.290
AND WE FOUND LYDIA'S BODY
UNDERNEATH YOUR BED,

34:53.292 --> 34:57.828
STUFFED INSIDE
ONE OF YOUR SON'S CELLO CASES.

34:57.830 --> 35:00.831
THANK GOD HE DOESN'T PLAY
THE TRIANGLE.

35:00.833 --> 35:04.801
[ SIGHS ]
I ASSUME YOU HAVE AN OFFER.

35:04.803 --> 35:07.404
A FAX
FROM ANDREA HOBBS...

35:07.406 --> 35:12.576
SAYING THAT IN EXCHANGE FOR
A CONFESSION TODAY, THIS MINUTE,

35:12.578 --> 35:14.611
SHE WILL TAKE DEATH
OFF THE TABLE

35:14.613 --> 35:16.780
AND SHE WILL GO STRAIGHT
TO LIFE WITHOUT PAROLE.

35:16.782 --> 35:20.150
NOW, CONSIDERING
THE INDIFFERENCE TO HUMAN LIFE

35:20.152 --> 35:23.120
AND THE NUMBER OF SPECIAL
CIRCUMSTANCES INVOLVED...

35:23.122 --> 35:24.521
THAT'S VERY GENEROUS.

35:24.523 --> 35:26.957
IF THE POLICE

35:26.959 --> 35:29.426
HAVE JUST ACCURATELY DESCRIBED
WHAT HAPPENED,

35:29.428 --> 35:30.794
YOU HAVE TWO CHOICES.

35:30.796 --> 35:34.397
ONE OF THEM IS DEATH ROW.
THE OTHER ISN'T.

35:34.399 --> 35:35.866
AND YOU'RE ON MY SIDE?

35:35.868 --> 35:37.934
I'M TRYING TO THINK OF
AN ALTERNATIVE EXPLANATION

35:37.936 --> 35:42.139
FOR A DEAD WOMAN UNDER YOUR BED
IN A CELLO CASE.

35:43.241 --> 35:44.741
BUT IT'S NOT COMING.

35:44.743 --> 35:47.611
AND THIS DEAL
WILL GO AWAY.

35:47.613 --> 35:50.614
TICK-TOCK,
MS. JORDAN.

35:50.616 --> 35:52.782
TICK-TOCK.

35:54.385 --> 35:57.888
YOU'VE HEARD
MY SON PLAY.

35:57.890 --> 36:01.691
HIS PRIVATE TEACHER SAYS
HE'S A GENIUS.

36:01.693 --> 36:04.194
THE INSTRUCTOR
AT HIS OLD SCHOOL

36:04.196 --> 36:07.697
[Laughing]
THINKS JOHN PHILIP SOUSA
IS A CLASSICAL COMPOSER.

36:07.699 --> 36:09.599
[ LAUGHS ]

36:10.801 --> 36:12.736
MYER HAS A CONSERVATORY

36:12.738 --> 36:15.906
FOR EXTRAORDINARILY
TALENTED CHILDREN,

36:15.908 --> 36:17.774
AND WHEN KEVIN WAS ACCEPTED,

36:17.776 --> 36:21.912
HIS FATHER SAID THAT
WE COULDN'T AFFORD IT...

36:21.914 --> 36:23.847
UNLESS $40,000
FELL IN OUR LAP.

36:23.849 --> 36:25.682
AND YOU KNEW WHERE
TO GET IT.

36:25.684 --> 36:29.252
DO YOU KNOW MUCH $120,000

36:29.254 --> 36:31.421
IS TO A COMPANY
LIKE McCORMICK SAVINGS?

36:31.423 --> 36:33.757
THAT'S THE COFFEE BUDGET,

36:33.759 --> 36:35.392
BUT FOR KEVIN,
THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE

36:35.394 --> 36:38.662
BETWEEN A BRILLIANT CAREER
AND GETTING LOST IN THE CROWD,

36:38.664 --> 36:41.064
AND I WAS -- I WAS NOT
GONNA LET THAT HAPPEN.

36:41.066 --> 36:45.969
SO, YOU MET DEAN AND LYDIA
AT YOUR GYM,

36:45.971 --> 36:47.938
AND YOU USED THEM
AS YOUR PUPPETS?

36:47.940 --> 36:49.239
OH, GOD!

36:49.241 --> 36:52.142
HOW MANY TIMES
DID WE GO OVER THE PLAN?

36:52.144 --> 36:54.110
THERE WAS NEVER
SUPPOSED TO BE A GUN.

36:54.112 --> 36:55.912
THAT WAS
COMPLETELY UNNECESSARY.

36:55.914 --> 36:59.115
IF THEY HAD JUST
DONE WHAT I TOLD THEM...

36:59.117 --> 37:02.719
IS THAT WHY YOU STRANGLED LYDIA?
'CAUSE SHE DISOBEYED YOU?

37:02.721 --> 37:05.989
LYDIA HAD
A COMPLETE MELTDOWN.

37:05.991 --> 37:07.724
SHE WANTED
TO TURN US BOTH IN.

37:07.726 --> 37:09.059
SHE FOUGHT WITH <i>ME,</i>

37:09.061 --> 37:11.728
AND I FOUGHT HER BACK BUT NOT --
NOT JUST FOR ME.

37:11.730 --> 37:13.096
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS --

37:13.098 --> 37:16.166
WHAT I DID TO LYDIA,
I DID THAT FOR MY SON,

37:16.168 --> 37:18.935
AND WHAT I DID
FOR MY SON [SNIFFLES]

37:18.937 --> 37:21.805
I DID THAT FOR THE WORLD.

37:30.181 --> 37:34.484
[ SIGHS ]
YOU SAID "LIFE"?

37:34.486 --> 37:38.822
LIFE IS GOOD
FOR THE WORLD, TOO.

37:41.259 --> 37:43.560
JUST WRITE THAT ALL DOWN,
MS. JORDAN,

37:43.562 --> 37:47.731
<i>BUT BE PREPARED TO SAY IT</i>
<i>OUT LOUD IN FRONT OF A JUDGE.</i>

37:49.667 --> 37:52.869
<i>DAD!</i>
<i>Sykes: GUYS,</i>
<i>KEVIN'S DAD IS HERE.</i>

37:52.871 --> 37:54.504
SOMEONE SHOULD TELL HIM
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH HIS WIFE.

37:54.506 --> 37:56.072
<i>OH, DAD,</i>
<i>I MISSED YOU SO MUCH!</i>
<i>YEAH.</i>

37:56.074 --> 37:57.274
JUST GIVE THE TWO OF THEM
A MINUTE TOGETHER

37:57.276 --> 37:59.976
BEFORE WE RUIN
CHRISTMAS FOREVER.

38:01.112 --> 38:03.246
<i>OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE</i>
<i>YOU'RE HERE.</i>

38:08.552 --> 38:10.353
Provenza: WELL, OF COURSE I KNOW
IT'S THE HOLIDAY PACKAGE!

38:10.355 --> 38:12.289
FINE. FINE!

38:13.391 --> 38:15.925
JUST -- JUST HANG ON.

38:15.927 --> 38:17.994
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]
I'M SORRY, PATRICE.

38:17.996 --> 38:20.230
UH, THEY SAY UNLESS
WE SHOW UP BY 10:00 P.M.

38:20.232 --> 38:22.032
THAT WE'LL LOSE IT ALL,

38:22.034 --> 38:24.701
AND I -- I STILL HAVE
A LOT OF WORK TO DO,

38:24.703 --> 38:27.370
SO, IF YOU DON'T MIND,
WOULD YOU --

38:27.372 --> 38:30.640
L-LOUIE, LOUIE,
WHERE WE ARE DOESN'T MATTER.

38:30.642 --> 38:32.108
ARE YOU SURE?

38:32.110 --> 38:35.378
I WASN'T GOING TO SPEND
CHRISTMAS WITH LAGUNA BEACH.

38:35.380 --> 38:37.213
I WAS GOING
TO SPEND IT WITH <i>YOU.</i>

38:37.215 --> 38:39.482
SO, IF WE'VE GOT
TO STAY IN TOWN,

38:39.484 --> 38:40.817
REALLY,
IT'S NO PROBLEM --

38:40.819 --> 38:43.653
WELL, NOT AT YOUR PLACE,
OF COURSE, BUT AT MINE,

38:43.655 --> 38:45.288
AND WE CAN PICK UP
A TURKEY,

38:45.290 --> 38:47.791
AND AS LONG AS
YOU DON'T MIND HELPING...

38:47.793 --> 38:49.726
[ Laughing ] WELL...

38:49.728 --> 38:51.361
MAN: Provenza?
Are you there?

38:51.363 --> 38:52.762
...THEN I'LL JUST,
UH, FIN--
Hello? Provenza?

38:52.764 --> 38:54.431
OH, OH, ONE SECOND.
YEAH.

38:54.433 --> 38:55.799
CANCEL IT.

38:55.801 --> 38:59.235
OH.
MM-HMM,
WITH THE FULL PENALTY.

38:59.837 --> 39:03.540
OH, AND MERRY CHRISTMAS
TO YOU, TOO.

39:03.542 --> 39:07.510
AND ALL THE REST OF
YOUR FELLOW REINDEER ASSHOLES.

39:07.512 --> 39:08.812
[ BEEP ]

39:09.313 --> 39:10.714
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

39:10.716 --> 39:11.948
COME IN.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

39:11.950 --> 39:15.251
UH, MEL JORDAN
IS THROUGH BOOKING,

39:15.253 --> 39:16.986
AND KEVIN'S BACK
WITH HIS DAD.

39:16.988 --> 39:19.189
GLAD SOMEONE
MADE IT HOME TONIGHT.

39:20.091 --> 39:21.291
UM...

39:21.293 --> 39:24.627
YOU KNOW, IF YOU CAN'T
MAKE IT HOME FOR THE HOLIDAYS,

39:24.629 --> 39:27.430
MAYBE HOME
CAN COME TO <i>YOU.</i>

39:27.432 --> 39:29.699
[ "OH, COME ALL YE FAITHFUL"
PLAYS ]

39:29.701 --> 39:31.201
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

39:32.603 --> 39:35.205
[ Laughing ]
OH, MY GOODNESS!

39:35.207 --> 39:36.606
LOOK AT THIS.

39:36.608 --> 39:38.375
OH,
THE CHRISTMAS VILLAGE.

39:38.377 --> 39:40.477
MM-HMM, SOME THINGS
DON'T CHANGE, MOM,

39:40.479 --> 39:42.479
INCLUDING THE CODE
AT YOUR STORAGE LOCKER.

39:42.481 --> 39:46.116
[ CHUCKLES ] THANKS
FOR BRINGING THE PARTY TO ME.

39:46.118 --> 39:49.219
OH, THIS IS --
THIS IS ALL SO WONDERFUL.

39:49.221 --> 39:52.255
LIEUTENANT.
[ CHUCKLES ] NICE HAT!

39:52.257 --> 39:54.324
WELL, I WAS GONNA WEAR
THE WHOLE SUIT,

39:54.326 --> 39:55.759
BUT PATRICE
WOULDN'T LET ME.

39:55.761 --> 39:57.727
I WAS AFRAID
HE MIGHT GET SHOT.

39:57.729 --> 39:59.396
[ LAUGHTER ]

40:00.331 --> 40:02.899
YOU CAN'T THINK OF ANYTHING
THAT WILL REMOVE THIS COLOR?

40:02.901 --> 40:05.001
I'M SORRY.
IT'LL WEAR OFF IN A FEW DAYS.

40:05.003 --> 40:07.303
A FEW --
HEY, AT LEAST THE GREEN
IS SEASONAL.

40:07.305 --> 40:09.172
[ SIGHS ]

40:09.174 --> 40:11.441
Flynn:
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

40:14.345 --> 40:15.912
UH...

40:15.914 --> 40:17.280
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

40:17.282 --> 40:18.915
EXCUSE ME.

40:18.917 --> 40:20.517
SURE.
THANKS.

40:23.754 --> 40:26.890
YOU TWO LOOK
A LITTLE LOST.

40:26.892 --> 40:29.526
THE PARTY IS IN HERE.

40:29.528 --> 40:30.894
ANYTHING WRONG?

40:30.896 --> 40:33.696
NO, MOM, NOTHING'S WRONG.
EVERYTHING IS GOOD.

40:33.698 --> 40:35.465
RUSTY?

40:37.034 --> 40:41.171
UH, I...DON'T REALLY THINK
IT'S MY PLACE TO SAY.

40:41.173 --> 40:43.106
SAY WHAT?
EMILY, WHAT?

40:43.108 --> 40:45.642
UH...

40:45.644 --> 40:46.776
THEY...

40:46.778 --> 40:49.245
THEY HELD BACK
MY CONTRACT

40:49.247 --> 40:52.248
BECAUSE THEY'RE MAKING ME
A SOLOIST NEXT YEAR.

40:52.250 --> 40:55.418
YEAH, I-I'M GONNA BE
THE NEXT SLEEPING BEAUTY.

40:55.420 --> 40:56.786
WHAT?
AND GISELLE.

40:56.788 --> 40:57.854
OH, MY GOD!

40:57.856 --> 40:59.956
[ LAUGHTER ]

40:59.958 --> 41:03.460
OH, MY GOD.
I'M SO HAPPY FOR YOU!

41:03.462 --> 41:05.261
OH, DEAR.

41:05.263 --> 41:07.363
[ GASPS ]
OH, MY GOODNESS.

41:07.365 --> 41:09.699
AH! THIS IS
SUCH GREAT NEWS.
[ LAUGHS ]

41:09.701 --> 41:11.201
Provenza: OKAY, OKAY,
LET'S GET INSIDE, EVERYBODY.

41:11.203 --> 41:13.636
IT'S TIME
TO MAKE A TOAST.

41:13.638 --> 41:15.271
ALL RIGHT,
EVERYBODY READY?

41:15.273 --> 41:17.907
ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.
ALTOGETHER NOW.

41:17.909 --> 41:20.944
All: HAPPY HOLIDAYS!

41:20.946 --> 41:23.413
CHEERS.
OH, CHEERS.

41:23.415 --> 41:24.681
[ LAUGHTER ]

41:24.683 --> 41:26.349
IT'S OKAY,
LITTLE BROTHER.

41:26.351 --> 41:27.383
HAPPY HOLIDAYS!

41:27.385 --> 41:29.819
WHAT MOM DOESN'T KNOW
WON'T HURT HER.

41:29.821 --> 41:31.855
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

41:31.857 --> 41:33.289
[ SIGHS ]
